15    /**
16    * Segment tree using objects and pointers. A segment tree is a tree data
17    * structure for storing intervals, or segments. It allows querying which of the
18    * stored segments contain a given point. It is, in principle, a static
19    * structure; that is, its content cannot be modified once the structure is
20    * built.
21    * <p>
22    * This class is meant to be somewhat generic, all you'd have to do is extend
23    * the Data abstract class to store your custom data. I've also included a range
24    * minimum, range maximum, range sum, and interval stabbing implementations.
25    * <p>
26    * @see <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Segment_tree">Segment Tree (Wikipedia)</a>
27    * <br>
28    * @author Justin Wetherell <phishman3579@gmail.com>
29    */
30    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
